      <accessrestrict id="aspace_47bb8ff2c6af82b931b393fde600a735">
         <head>Conditions Governing Access</head>
         <p>This collection is open for research. The finding aid includes links to stream most interviews online via Oral History of American Music's (OHAM) AV access system, Aviary. Yale users can connect to the Yale VPN to stream these interviews without restriction. Other users are able to request access to interviews directly through Aviary. For access instructions, and to request transcripts of an interview, see <ref href="https://guides.library.yale.edu/oham/collectionsguide/access">OHAM's website.</ref>
         </p>  
      </accessrestrict>
      <userestrict id="aspace_b38776cc93bc5266edbb5bb516de197f">
         <head>Conditions Governing Use</head>
         <p>Rights and permissions for Oral History of American Music materials vary between individual interviews. Researchers wishing to publish or broadcast Oral History of American Music materials are responsible for obtaining direct authorization from copyright holders: generally, the interviewees or their estates.</p>  
      </userestrict>
